    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>The California Avenue Congregational Church was first gathered in 1883. Construction on a
        brick church building, located at 101 S. California Avenue, was completed in 1887. Changing
        demographics in the East Garfield Park neighborhood meant that the congregation was
        struggling to maintain membership by the 1910s. In 1918, the church federated with the
        Monroe Street Church of Christ to form the Monroe Street Federated Church. The church
        dissolved in 1933.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection primarily contains administrative and membership related records from the
        California Avenue Congregational Church in Chicago, Illinois. The collection includes church
        meeting minutes, vital membership records, including baptismal and marriage records, a 1918
        edition of the church's newsletter, and a 1935 directory of the church's membership.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>Materials in this collection have been arranged in chronological order by start date.</p>
    </arrangement>
